cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.OH

The paper deals with optimization problems and proposes a novel approach that uses meta-models to address computationally expensive subproblems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Divide and Conquer (cs.DC), or Optimization and Control (cs.OH) sub-categories. However, since the paper focuses on optimization and meta-models, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. cs.AI is also likely since the paper proposes a new approach to solving optimization problems. cs.DC and cs.OH are less likely but still possible since the paper deals with high-dimensional optimization problems and the use of meta-models to address subproblems.
